l say again, abort mission. Out.

717
01:23:10,563 --> 01:23:13,224
150 armed men, huh?

718
01:23:34,183 --> 01:23:35,877
Raise your arms, please.

719
01:23:51,631 --> 01:23:55,567
Thank you for responding to my note.
And so promptly.

720
01:23:56,568 --> 01:24:00,436
l had nothing to do
with the death of Mr Jacobs.

721
01:24:00,605 --> 01:24:05,064
lt was an act of madness. But
a typical one from the men l work for.

722
01:24:06,844 --> 01:24:10,746
- What do you want?
- Same as you. Mineral water.

723
01:24:11,681 --> 01:24:16,640
Do we agree that as long as Americans
demand drugs, they will be supplied?

724
01:24:16,818 --> 01:24:19,412
l don't want to be here
longer than l have to.

725
01:24:19,588 --> 01:24:23,183
You mentioned a gang war.
What does that mean?

726
01:24:23,357 --> 01:24:27,919
- That we want the same thing.
- Really?

727
01:24:28,094 --> 01:24:33,031
So far you've done all the work.
You've taken care of the little fish.

728
01:24:33,199 --> 01:24:35,258
l will take care of the one that got away.

729
01:24:36,002 --> 01:24:40,995
Once Escobedo is gone,
l will be in a position to help you.

730
01:24:41,173 --> 01:24:45,370
- You want to help me?
- Your country. Your people.

731
01:24:45,543 --> 01:24:50,275
By restructuring the drug trade.
By regulating it.

732
01:24:51,648 --> 01:24:57,177
What would you say if l promised you
l'd halve cocaine shipments to the US?

733
01:24:58,822 --> 01:25:03,052
l'd say you'd been using
too much of your product.

734
01:25:03,224 --> 01:25:06,786
l can also give you regular quotas
on major arrests

735
01:25:06,961 --> 01:25:10,157
that your police can take credit for.

736
01:25:10,331 --> 01:25:14,028
lmagine. Dramatic seizures.
Drastic reductions.

737
01:25:14,201 --> 01:25:18,933
No more senseless violence.
You'll have your victory.

738
01:25:23,343 --> 01:25:24,935
ln return for what?

739
01:25:26,244 --> 01:25:30,145
l also need a victory,
to establish my position

740
01:25:30,314 --> 01:25:34,978
with what is left of the cartel,
so l can help you.

741
01:25:35,720 --> 01:25:40,588
l need to defeat those soldiers
blowing up everything they see.

742
01:25:40,757 --> 01:25:46,525
Give me maps of their locations.
Cut off their communications.

743
01:25:53,568 --> 01:25:59,302
DEA's sending the audio
surveillance tape. l haven't got it yet.

744
01:26:01,941 --> 01:26:07,277
You know what you think about...
when you're lying here?

745
01:26:08,647 --> 01:26:11,810
You know you're gonna die,
and you think...

746
01:26:13,786 --> 01:26:18,518
...that's all right. You lived a long time.

747
01:26:18,690 --> 01:26:20,782
You had a family that loved you.

748
01:26:21,191 --> 01:26:25,490
You had a job that you thought
made a difference.

749
01:26:26,396 --> 01:26:29,194
That you thought was honourable.

750
01:26:30,166 --> 01:26:32,964
And then you see this.

751
01:26:36,971 --> 01:26:40,839
l'm afraid if l dig any deeper...

752
01:26:41,008 --> 01:26:43,602
...no one's gonna like what l find.

753
01:26:49,449 --> 01:26:52,781
You took an oath...

754
01:26:52,951 --> 01:26:55,044
...if you recall...

755
01:26:57,890 --> 01:27:01,416
...when you first came to work for me.

756
01:27:01,593 --> 01:27:07,325
And l don't mean to the National
Security Advisor of the United States,

757
01:27:08,532 --> 01:27:11,797
l mean to his boss.

758
01:27:11,968 --> 01:27:14,458
And l don't mean the President.

759
01:27:16,104 --> 01:27:19,403
You gave your word to...

760
01:27:21,010 --> 01:27:23,602
...his boss.

761
01:27:23,777 --> 01:27:26,371
You gave your word...

762
01:27:26,547 --> 01:27:31,006
...to the people of the United States.

763
01:27:32,286 --> 01:27:35,083
Your word is who you are.

764
01:27:40,358 --> 01:27:41,882
What else have you got there?

765
01:27:48,165 --> 01:27:51,225
l brought you some new magazines.

766
01:28:00,742 --> 01:28:06,577
The situation in East Timor seems
to have stabilised during the day.

767
01:28:06,747 --> 01:28:10,547
- ls that it?
- Except for the other thing.

768
01:28:12,018 --> 01:28:15,078
We've accomplished a lot,
we're seeing tangible results.

769
01:28:15,255 --> 01:28:18,985
Drug shipments are down.
The price on the street is rising.

770
01:28:19,158 --> 01:28:23,594
The administration is perceived
to be doing something right.

771
01:28:23,762 --> 01:28:26,730
What's the bad news?

772
01:28:28,501 --> 01:28:34,131
l'm worried about the car bomb coming
so soon after Jacobs' assassination.

773
01:28:36,006 --> 01:28:38,736
Just the kind of thing reporters live for.

774
01:28:38,909 --> 01:28:43,037
- They'd love to make a connection.
- And you think they will?

775
01:28:44,479 --> 01:28:48,609
l think it's time
the whole thing went away.

776
01:28:48,783 --> 01:28:52,219
- lf that's what you think.
- l think so.

777
01:28:54,288 --> 01:28:58,816
Then it should go away.
lt never happened.

778
01:29:00,327 --> 01:29:02,294
Yes, sir.

779
01:29:03,796 --> 01:29:07,459
Well...it's possible.

780
01:29:07,634 --> 01:29:12,797
lt would be easier if you told me whose
system you wanted me to break into.

781
01:29:12,970 --> 01:29:14,939
- Morning, Dr Ryan.
- Morning.

782
01:29:36,491 --> 01:29:39,220
We're way beyond birthdays now.

783
01:29:40,194 --> 01:29:44,653
l'm gonna have to write
a special program here.

784
01:29:55,440 --> 01:29:59,375
OK, sweetheart, let's get to work.

785
01:30:00,311 --> 01:30:02,211
Fine, good.

786
01:30:03,647 --> 01:30:07,378
Yes... Here we go.

787
01:31:04,699 --> 01:31:07,691
Reciprocity. What's that?

788
01:31:20,580 --> 01:31:23,447
l forgot to tell you, after you get the code,

789
01:31:23,615 --> 01:31:28,483
wait until he's off his system
before you log on. He will know.

790
01:31:28,653 --> 01:31:31,019
Jesus, Petey, it's too late.

791
01:31:31,188 --> 01:31:33,587
Oh, my God...

792
01:32:04,217 --> 01:32:05,877
Cutter...

793
01:32:20,563 --> 01:32:24,897
- Bob, Jack Ryan here.
- Good morning, Jack.

794
01:32:25,401 --> 01:32:29,427
Listen, maybe we got off to a bad start.

795
01:32:30,206 --> 01:32:34,732
lf we're gonna work together,
we should get to know each other.

796
01:32:34,910 --> 01:32:39,073
Do you play tennis?
Tennis? Do you play tennis?

797
01:32:39,245 --> 01:32:43,648
- Yeah, l play tennis.
- How about we get together?

798
01:32:43,817 --> 01:32:47,115
Next week?
Maybe an hour before we start work?

799
01:32:54,259 --> 01:32:56,318
- Jack?
- Yeah.

800
01:32:56,994 --> 01:33:01,488
Computer theft is a serious crime.

801
01:33:04,701 --> 01:33:07,999
So are crimes against the Constitution.

802
01:33:09,606 --> 01:33:11,664
Son of a bitch!

803
01:33:23,551 --> 01:33:25,541
Son of a bitch!

804
01:33:29,722 --> 01:33:31,121
Come on, come on.

805
01:33:34,426 --> 01:33:36,087
Clark...

806
01:34:12,325 --> 01:34:13,986
You're going to jail, pal.

807
01:34:15,529 --> 01:34:19,259
What is that?
What do you think you have there?

808
01:34:19,431 --> 01:34:21,023
You broke the law.

809
01:34:22,233 --> 01:34:26,192
You are such a Boy Scout.

810
01:34:26,371 --> 01:34:29,772
Look at you.
You see everything in black and white.

811
01:34:29,941 --> 01:34:33,899
No, not black and white, Ritter.
Right and wrong!

812
01:34:34,076 --> 01:34:38,604
- You see! There you go again.
- Why was l kept out of it?

813
01:34:38,781 --> 01:34:42,045
You weren't, you're neck deep in it.
You went before Congress.

814
01:34:42,217 --> 01:34:45,084
You got the money for it.
You lied under oath...

815
01:34:45,253 --> 01:34:50,053
- l never lied to Congress!
- You told them no troops.

816
01:34:50,224 --> 01:34:53,625
- There are troops!
- You know l didn't know that.

817
01:34:53,794 --> 01:34:59,459
No. l have no recollection of that.
That's the term you have to learn.

818
01:34:59,632 --> 01:35:03,658
- Who authorised this?
- Sure, they'll ask you that.

819
01:35:03,836 --> 01:35:08,568
- Who authorised this?
- l have no recollection...Senator.

820
01:35:13,711 --> 01:35:18,079
l did not sign up for somebody's
bullshit political agenda.

821
01:35:18,248 --> 01:35:22,207
Who authorised this? Cutter?

822
01:35:22,385 --> 01:35:25,876
Cutter couldn't tie his shoes
without permission.

823
01:35:30,326 --> 01:35:33,783
- lf l go down, you're going with me.
- Wrong again.

824
01:35:33,962 --> 01:35:37,488
l have an autographed
''Get Out of Jail Free'' card.

825
01:35:39,466 --> 01:35:43,765
''The President authorises
the Deputy Director ClA, Robert Ritter,

826
01:35:43,936 --> 01:35:49,374
''to conduct Operation Reciprocity
including all support necessary.

827
01:35:49,542 --> 01:35:56,104
''This operation is deemed important
to the national security of the US.''

828
01:35:58,149 --> 01:36:02,642
You don't have one of these,
do you, Jack?

829
01:36:11,793 --> 01:36:16,820
Grey! The world's grey, Jack!

830
01:36:49,192 --> 01:36:54,287
You have any idea how l'm gonna
get out of this mess?

831
01:36:54,463 --> 01:36:57,557
Absolutely none.

832
01:37:06,240 --> 01:37:10,073
Yeah. This is he.

833
01:37:14,046 --> 01:37:15,742
When?

834
01:37:20,419 --> 01:37:22,614
James?

835
01:37:24,156 --> 01:37:26,385
Thank you.

836
01:37:26,557 --> 01:37:34,190
Admiral James Greer devoted his life
to his country and his family.

837
01:37:34,364 --> 01:37:38,494
Giving selflessly
of both his wisdom and his love.

838
01:37:39,735 --> 01:37:43,569
He served his country
for more than 50 years.

839
01:37:43,739 --> 01:37:48,937
Enlisting in the Navy at 17.
Graduating from the Academy.

840
01:37:49,110 --> 01:37:52,704
Achieving three stars for his flag.

841
01:37:52,879 --> 01:37:56,610
He lived through tumultuous events
in his country's life.

842
01:37:56,783 --> 01:38:01,185
He participated in them.
He made them clearer to the rest of us,

843
01:38:01,354 --> 01:38:07,781
with his knowledge, his honesty,
his integrity and his courage.

844
01:38:16,934 --> 01:38:18,697
l can't see them, but l know they're there.

845
01:38:19,535 --> 01:38:22,868
Five kilometres due east
from your position.

846
01:38:27,776 --> 01:38:31,303
Keep pushing forward. We'll trap them.

847
01:38:31,480 --> 01:38:34,777
Never was he deluded
into thinking that one man...

848
01:38:35,750 --> 01:38:38,183
...could solve the ills of the world.

849
01:38:38,351 --> 01:38:43,050
Always the soldier, on the battlefields
of the South Pacific, Korea...

850
01:38:43,223 --> 01:38:47,886
...Vietnam and Washington,
he fought as part of a unit...

851
01:38:48,527 --> 01:38:50,391
... to preserve the ideals...

852
01:38:50,561 --> 01:38:51,960
Knife, this is Variable.

853
01:38:52,130 --> 01:38:54,030
...of his nation.

854
01:38:54,198 --> 01:38:57,167
Knife! This is Variable. Over.

855
01:38:58,135 --> 01:39:02,231
To the refuge of the earth,
we entrust our friend's body.

856
01:39:02,706 --> 01:39:07,108
To the protection of our God
in Heaven, we entrust his soul.

857
01:39:07,276 --> 01:39:11,837
To ourselves, we entrust his spirit...

858
01:39:12,013 --> 01:39:15,676
...and the principles he lived by.

859
01:39:15,850 --> 01:39:17,784
We're gonna miss you, James.

860
01:39:40,605 --> 01:39:42,265
Variable, this is Knife, over.

861
01:39:43,607 --> 01:39:46,700
Variable, this is Knife, over.

862
01:39:46,876 --> 01:39:50,368
Variable, l am not receiving.
We are under heavy attack.

863
01:39:50,547 --> 01:39:53,811
Need air support, over.

864
01:40:15,167 --> 01:40:18,863
Variable, this is Knife, over! Switch!

865
01:40:51,432 --> 01:40:55,424
Variable, this is Knife!
Where the hell are you?!

866
01:41:16,920 --> 01:41:21,322
On behalf of a grateful nation,
our condolences.

867
01:41:21,491 --> 01:41:24,687
- He was a very great patriot.
- Thank you.

868
01:42:03,426 --> 01:42:07,759
- Hello?
- Jean Fowler for Dr Jack Ryan.

869
01:42:07,930 --> 01:42:11,366
Jack? You've got to hear this.

870
01:42:11,533 --> 01:42:13,966
Picked it up this morning.

871
01:42:14,135 --> 01:42:20,095
Variable, this is Knife.
We are under attack, need air support.

872
01:42:20,273 --> 01:42:23,470
Variable, this is Knife,
where the hell are you?

873
01:42:24,144 --> 01:42:27,170
Jack, what do you want me
to do with this?

874
01:42:28,180 --> 01:42:32,742
Make a copy, Jean. Make ten copies.

875
01:42:32,917 --> 01:42:35,852
Get them to me
as quick as you can. Thanks.

876
01:42:38,488 --> 01:42:42,822
Jesus. They're going to leave
those guys down there.

877
01:43:26,163 --> 01:43:31,998
He's on American 915.
He'll be in Bogota 7.50 p.m.

878
01:43:44,312 --> 01:43:46,212
-Yeah?
- lt's Ritter.

879
01:43:46,381 --> 01:43:50,180
- Where the fuck have you been?
- We have a problem.

880
01:43:50,350 --> 01:43:53,080
We've got a disaster!
l can't get through to my men.

881
01:43:53,687 --> 01:43:56,985
We had to shut down the satellite link.

882
01:43:58,824 --> 01:44:01,190
- Clark?
- You had to what?

883
01:44:03,094 --> 01:44:09,055
lt's Ryan. He found out everything.
He threatened to tell Congress

884
01:44:09,366 --> 01:44:12,301
if we didn't shut down the operation.

885
01:44:12,469 --> 01:44:17,997
OK. lt's shut down. Just give me
some air and my men are out of there.

886
01:44:19,342 --> 01:44:26,179
Clark, maybe you're not hearing me.
There is no air. We are shut down.

887
01:44:27,481 --> 01:44:31,042
l'm on a plane. l'm gonna kill him.

888
01:44:32,320 --> 01:44:33,684
Ritter?

889
01:44:36,323 --> 01:44:38,757
He's coming to you.

890
01:44:39,192 --> 01:44:42,889
American Airlines at 19.50
with no security.

891
01:44:43,062 --> 01:44:47,624
- Who is this?
- National Security Advisor Cutter.

892
01:44:47,800 --> 01:44:50,359
Once Ryan's gone, we're back on line.

893
01:44:50,903 --> 01:44:52,733
You understand?

894
01:44:54,172 --> 01:44:56,299
Yes, sir.

895
01:46:17,342 --> 01:46:18,707
Clark...

896
01:46:18,877 --> 01:46:20,606
- Jesus!
- Get in the van.

897
01:46:20,779 --> 01:46:25,340
- Don't do this, l came to find you.
- You found me. Get in.

898
01:46:29,719 --> 01:46:31,414
Behind the wheel.

899
01:46:32,922 --> 01:46:34,389
Clark...

900
01:46:35,858 --> 01:46:37,586
Drive.

901
01:47:05,583 --> 01:47:08,177
- Ritter.
- Ryan's dead.

902
01:47:10,254 --> 01:47:12,312
How?

903
01:47:12,489 --> 01:47:15,616
l killed him. Turn the satellite back on.

904
01:47:19,128 --> 01:47:23,894
You said get rid of Ryan
and we're back in business, right?

905
01:47:49,087 --> 01:47:51,111
What the hell are you doing here?

906
01:47:53,524 --> 01:47:56,687
l came to help you get those guys out.

907
01:47:58,329 --> 01:48:00,921
What can you do to help me?

908
01:48:06,602 --> 01:48:09,570
What do you need?

909
01:48:09,737 --> 01:48:11,103
A helicopter.

910
01:48:13,374 --> 01:48:15,342
A helicopter.

911
01:48:24,517 --> 01:48:25,848
No, thank you.

912
01:48:28,820 --> 01:48:31,880
- ls this ''Happy Hour''?
- lt's always ''Happy Hour''.

913
01:48:32,056 --> 01:48:35,719
- Your pilot owns this joint?
- He lives here.

914
01:48:41,565 --> 01:48:42,896
Here he is.

915
01:48:54,276 --> 01:48:58,871
Morning. l'm here to rent the Huey.

916
01:48:59,046 --> 01:49:03,176
Sorry, we don't rent it any more.
But it is for sale.

917
01:49:04,851 --> 01:49:06,716
How much is it?

918
01:49:08,120 --> 01:49:10,520
Two million dollars.

919
01:49:16,327 --> 01:49:18,955
My pilot and l would
have to do a test flight.

920
01:49:19,131 --> 01:49:22,099
Of course.
You just have to leave a deposit.

921
01:49:24,000 --> 01:49:25,831
How much is that?

922
01:49:26,002 --> 01:49:27,492
Two million dollars.

923
01:49:33,242 --> 01:49:36,177
Would you take a company cheque?

924
01:49:43,117 --> 01:49:44,607
Yes.

925
01:49:52,558 --> 01:49:56,255
- Here we go.
- Big son of a bitch, ain't she?

926
01:49:58,496 --> 01:50:02,761
- Do you have any time in this type?
- Nine o'clock.

927
01:50:12,842 --> 01:50:19,007
- Get out of my chopper.
- No. My chopper. Let's go.

928
01:50:39,531 --> 01:50:42,659
Their last communication put them here.

929
01:50:43,936 --> 01:50:48,998
The closest extraction point is here.
ln this gorge.

930
01:50:49,906 --> 01:50:51,636
l got it.

931
01:51:11,593 --> 01:51:14,925
- ls that a body down there?
- Yes.

932
01:51:16,964 --> 01:51:20,490
- One of ours?
- One of mine.

933
01:51:24,036 --> 01:51:28,268
Find a place to set her down.
We'll look for the others.

934
01:52:11,910 --> 01:52:16,779
Nowhere to run to. No place to hide.

935
01:52:16,948 --> 01:52:22,647
Blood trails everywhere.
They all lead to the river.

936
01:52:35,263 --> 01:52:39,392
These are the falls we saw from the air.

937
01:52:39,567 --> 01:52:43,162
The bodies should be
about 50 metres down.

938
01:52:55,481 --> 01:53:00,417
You left us!
You left us with no support at all!

939
01:53:00,586 --> 01:53:04,885
You left us out to dry!
You son of a bitch!

940
01:53:07,657 --> 01:53:11,092
- lt's not his fault.
- Whose fault is it?

941
01:53:13,095 --> 01:53:14,426
lt's my fault.

942
01:53:20,002 --> 01:53:22,060
lt's my fault.

943
01:53:34,148 --> 01:53:38,083
l was on point
when the last attack came.

944
01:53:39,084 --> 01:53:41,211
Over a mile away.

945
01:53:42,420 --> 01:53:44,751
By the time l got back it was over.

946
01:53:46,158 --> 01:53:49,320
They were taken to Captain Rosso.

947
01:53:50,493 --> 01:53:53,224
The others?

948
01:53:53,397 --> 01:53:55,091
l buried them.

949
01:54:04,206 --> 01:54:06,071
Road to the town.

950
01:54:06,241 --> 01:54:09,607
They loaded the prisoners here.
Blood everywhere.

951
01:54:09,777 --> 01:54:13,645
- God knows where they are now.
- Escobedo knows.

952
01:54:13,815 --> 01:54:17,113
What are you going to do?
Knock on his door?

953
01:54:23,756 --> 01:54:28,715
Morning. l'd like to see Ernesto
Escobedo. l don't have an appointment.

954
01:54:42,271 --> 01:54:44,102
OK.

955
01:54:46,175 --> 01:54:48,040
Hands up.

956
01:54:48,743 --> 01:54:50,904
Hands up!

957
01:54:52,246 --> 01:54:54,180
Wallet.

958
01:54:58,985 --> 01:55:00,613
lt's a tape recorder.

959
01:55:05,358 --> 01:55:07,416
He's in.

960
01:55:10,829 --> 01:55:13,559
Bird, this is Variable, over.

961
01:55:15,300 --> 01:55:19,099
Bird, this is Variable, over.

962
01:55:35,483 --> 01:55:39,078
Dr Ryan... Come in.

963
01:55:53,065 --> 01:55:56,761
Sit down. What can l do for you?

964
01:55:58,169 --> 01:56:04,198
l didn't know who else to turn to.
l have a problem.

965
01:56:05,108 --> 01:56:08,805
An associate of mine,
a coffee buyer and his assistant

966
01:56:08,978 --> 01:56:11,776
were on a business trip in this area.

967
01:56:11,947 --> 01:56:15,678
They disappeared yesterday.
l'm very concerned.

968
01:56:15,852 --> 01:56:18,149
Coffee buyer?

969
01:56:18,320 --> 01:56:20,982
lt's very important to me to find them.

970
01:56:21,156 --> 01:56:24,454
Coffee buying is becoming
a dangerous business.

971
01:56:25,760 --> 01:56:30,924
Yes. Well, it was for Peter Hardin.

972
01:56:33,399 --> 01:56:37,028
- Who?
- He was a client of Lindo Coffee.

973
01:56:37,202 --> 01:56:42,162
- Lindo Coffee has many clients.
- You must have heard of this one.

974
01:56:42,340 --> 01:56:45,901
He owed your company
a great deal of money.

975
01:56:46,076 --> 01:56:50,206
l'll have to talk to Accounting about that.

976
01:56:51,548 --> 01:56:53,913
650 million dollars.

977
01:56:57,053 --> 01:56:59,283
And change.

978
01:57:00,723 --> 01:57:05,989
Are you offering to help me
with the collection of an unpaid debt?

979
01:57:06,161 --> 01:57:09,061
- No.
- What are you offering?

980
01:57:10,531 --> 01:57:15,297
A trade. Felix Cortez has sold you out.

981
01:57:15,468 --> 01:57:19,733
He will murder you and your family,
and take over the cartel.

982
01:57:19,905 --> 01:57:21,770
Where's my tape recorder?

983
01:57:28,379 --> 01:57:30,176
Play the tape.

984
01:58:04,010 --> 01:58:05,704
Let's move.

985
01:58:35,636 --> 01:58:39,037
l'd like you to meet
my new friend, Dr Ryan.

986
01:58:39,206 --> 01:58:42,437
A doctor? Why? ls somebody sick?

987
01:58:56,054 --> 01:58:57,521
What does he want?

988
01:58:59,689 --> 01:59:03,216
The safe return of his associates.

989
01:59:03,394 --> 01:59:07,591
And what does he offer us in return?

990
01:59:07,764 --> 01:59:10,095
You.

991
01:59:16,037 --> 01:59:20,201
Whatever this man has told you is a lie.
He lies for a living.

992
01:59:20,375 --> 01:59:24,936
He's in the intelligence business.
You're in the intelligence business!

993
01:59:31,517 --> 01:59:34,349
You've taken care of the little fish.

994
01:59:34,519 --> 01:59:36,749
l'll take care of the one that got away.

995
01:59:37,289 --> 01:59:42,123
Once Escobedo is gone,
l'll be in a position to help you.

996
01:59:42,293 --> 01:59:46,423
So, the question is...

997
01:59:47,731 --> 01:59:50,062
...what am l supposed to do with you?

998
01:59:53,670 --> 01:59:56,433
l guess l'm supposed to
kill you with this bat!

999
02:00:05,347 --> 02:00:07,279
Get up.

1000
02:00:11,985 --> 02:00:16,354
Dramatic seizures.
Drastic reductions, no more violence...

1001
02:00:16,522 --> 02:00:18,615
You'll have your victory.

1002
02:00:20,359 --> 02:00:23,055
ln return for what?

1003
02:01:02,661 --> 02:01:04,595
- Where are they?
- They're here.

1004
02:01:07,432 --> 02:01:11,368
The American killed Ernesto! Let's go!

1005
02:01:59,543 --> 02:02:01,773
Bird to Variable. Over.

1006
02:02:15,224 --> 02:02:19,922
Bird, this is Variable.
Where the hell are you?

1007
02:02:20,094 --> 02:02:23,689
l'm cruising about five klicks
south of the village.

1008
02:02:24,464 --> 02:02:29,163
- Stay there. l'll get back to you.
- Roger that.

1009
02:02:40,945 --> 02:02:43,379
- No one.
- The prisoners!

1010
02:03:30,120 --> 02:03:32,851
Come on, guys. Let's go, son.

1011
02:03:34,491 --> 02:03:36,356
We're going home, boys.

1012
02:04:50,122 --> 02:04:52,681
Pick us up at the Lindo Coffee factory.

1013
02:06:29,273 --> 02:06:33,266
Not only can l expose you
to the press, so can the soldiers.

1014
02:06:33,443 --> 02:06:40,041
Do you want to take your chances
with the courts and the reporters?

1015
02:06:40,215 --> 02:06:44,241
To end the political career
of your commander-in-chief?

1016
02:07:28,823 --> 02:07:31,087
Let's go!

1017
02:07:58,382 --> 02:08:02,078
Get your asses in here!
Come on, we got to go!

1018
02:08:05,020 --> 02:08:08,148
Come on!

1019
02:08:13,761 --> 02:08:16,457
Hold it! We wait for Ryan!

1020
02:08:16,631 --> 02:08:18,155
Yeah? We're out of here!

1021
02:08:25,572 --> 02:08:28,506
Set it down! He's down there!

1022
02:08:41,119 --> 02:08:43,143
Come on!

1023
02:09:01,769 --> 02:09:03,397
l've got you!

1024
02:09:10,410 --> 02:09:12,435
Chavez, cover me!

1025
02:09:21,652 --> 02:09:23,677
Your hand. Give me your hand!

1026
02:10:30,778 --> 02:10:33,770
The President will see you now.

1027
02:10:46,090 --> 02:10:49,060
Jack! l'm glad you're here.

1028
02:10:50,528 --> 02:10:54,555
Sit down. Can l get you anything?

1029
02:10:54,732 --> 02:10:56,323
No.

1030
02:10:57,367 --> 02:11:01,667
- Come on, sit down.
- l would prefer to stand, sir.

1031
02:11:04,106 --> 02:11:10,271
Some things have gone on here
that l'm just becoming aware of.

1032
02:11:10,445 --> 02:11:14,676
l was kept in the dark, as you were,
for a very long time.

1033
02:11:14,848 --> 02:11:18,113
- Troubling things.
- Yeah.

1034
02:11:18,285 --> 02:11:22,618
Now we have to sort them out,
figure out who's responsible for what.

1035
02:11:22,789 --> 02:11:26,588
And what to do about it.
And we have to do it delicately,

1036
02:11:26,758 --> 02:11:29,592
otherwise people might
get the wrong idea.

1037
02:11:30,929 --> 02:11:32,260
We have to lie.

1038
02:11:34,366 --> 02:11:38,734
- Did l say that?
- No, you didn't.

1039
02:11:38,903 --> 02:11:42,532
- You're upset.
- l'm upset.

1040
02:11:42,707 --> 02:11:48,076
lt's understandable. Do you mind
if l give you a bit of advice?

1041
02:11:48,244 --> 02:11:50,711
Of course, you know this. You're smart.

1042
02:11:50,879 --> 02:11:54,336
Never make important decisions
while you're upset.

1043
02:11:55,316 --> 02:12:00,686
You did. American soldiers and
innocent civilians are dead because of it.

1044
02:12:00,855 --> 02:12:05,052
- l never ordered any...
- Don't you play that game with me!

1045
02:12:05,225 --> 02:12:09,126
Do not dishonour their memories
by pretending you didn't know!

1046
02:12:09,295 --> 02:12:12,856
- How dare you lecture me!
- How dare you, sir!

1047
02:12:13,032 --> 02:12:17,161
How dare you come here and bark at me
like some little junkyard dog!

1048
02:12:17,335 --> 02:12:20,497
l am the President of the United States!

1049
02:12:24,541 --> 02:12:27,408
lt gives me no pleasure to do it, sir.

1050
02:12:28,411 --> 02:12:31,539
As acting Deputy Director
of lntelligence, it is my duty

1051
02:12:31,714 --> 02:12:35,616
to report this matter
to the Senate Oversight Committee.

1052
02:12:40,655 --> 02:12:46,388
- You're not going to do that.
- l'm not?

1053
02:12:48,862 --> 02:12:52,628
You've got yourself
a chip in the big game now.

1054
02:12:54,067 --> 02:12:59,663
You're going to save that for a time
when your own ass is on the line.

1055
02:13:00,239 --> 02:13:03,230
And then you're going to pull it out.

1056
02:13:03,408 --> 02:13:07,605
And l'm going to cash it in for you.
Right?

1057
02:13:09,679 --> 02:13:13,115
l don't think l have anything more
to say to you, sir.

1058
02:13:14,518 --> 02:13:19,955
The country can't afford another
scandal, Jack. To protect itself,

1059
02:13:20,122 --> 02:13:25,821
it won't allow another deception
that goes all the way to the top.

1060
02:13:25,994 --> 02:13:29,987
You'll take the blame.
Cutter and Ritter will take some too,

1061
02:13:30,164 --> 02:13:33,395
but it will only amount to
a slap on the wrist.

1062
02:13:33,567 --> 02:13:37,560
Then 20,000 dollars an hour
on the lecture circuit.

1063
02:13:38,738 --> 02:13:42,834
The rest of the blame will fall on Greer.

1064
02:13:43,009 --> 02:13:46,705
Oh yeah, you'll take him down with you.

1065
02:13:46,878 --> 02:13:48,971
You'll destroy his reputation.

1066
02:13:49,581 --> 02:13:55,176
But that's as far as it will go.
The old Potomac two-step, Jack.

1067
02:13:58,121 --> 02:14:01,818
l'm sorry, Mr President, l don't dance.

1068
02:14:25,277 --> 02:14:27,370
Ryan, have you got a minute?

1069
02:14:27,546 --> 02:14:29,343
No.

1070
02:14:30,349 --> 02:14:33,146
We need to talk!

1071
02:14:33,318 --> 02:14:35,285
Ryan!

1072
02:14:59,573 --> 02:15:05,238
The Committee will come to order.
The chair will now call Dr John Ryan.

1073
02:15:26,163 --> 02:15:32,031
Dr Ryan, thank you for appearing
before the Committee today.

1074
02:15:32,835 --> 02:15:35,531
Please stand and raise your right hand.

1075
02:15:39,407 --> 02:15:43,365
Do you solemnly swear
that the testimony you're about to give

1076
02:15:43,544 --> 02:15:47,877
is the whole truth and nothing
but the truth, so help you God?

1077
02:15:51,151 --> 02:15:53,084
l do.

1078
02:15:54,220 --> 02:15:58,452
Dr Ryan, you may consider yourself
under oath. Please be seated.


